7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Gemini and Perplexity share a solid foundation of core features including Web Search, File Upload, Image Generation, Api Access. Where Gemini pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Code Execution and Voice Input and Plugins and Memory, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Gemini holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Perplexity scores 8/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Gemini and Perplexity offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Gemini's free tier and Perplexity's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
