b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Gemini is best suited for Google workspace users, multimodal tasks, research, coding, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Perplexity, meanwhile, shines for research, fact checking, current events, cited answers, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Gemini describes itself as \"Google's multimodal AI chatbot with deep Google integration.\" Perplexity, established in 2022, positions itself as \"AI-powered search engine that cites every source.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Gemini** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (10 vs 6), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Perplexity is a poor choice — far from it. Perplexity excels in its own right, particularly for research and fact checking.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value deep integration with google services, go with Gemini. If every answer includes cited sources matters more to you, Perplexity is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
